As a fellow creative, I will always say that when a passion starts to feel like work, it's time to take a break. You guys provided me and countless others with years of entertainment.

Not every joke landed, not every punchline worked, but every episode was hilarious. It's rare, especially for a comedy, that is as consistent as DBZA. You should be proud of the show you created, and that you ended on a high note.

It's so rare for a show to end well, and you guys nailed it. Thank you.

snippet.textDisplay:
11 years can not seem like much but in reality it can be a massive amount of history and full of life in a short period. In the time I’ve watched DBZA, from finding it in 2009 as a 6th grader to now, a college graduate, it’s surreal to grow, change, and morph into life with something like this. Thank you TFS, for all the experiences you’ve given to countless fans, including me, the chance to watch a small channel making abridged shorts of a beloved franchise grow into a something that was once thought impossible. We all support you in your future endeavors.

Favorite quote: “It goes you, the dirt, the worms inside the dirt, Popo’s stool, Kami, then Popo. Any questions?”

snippet.textDisplay:
I want to thank TFS for DBZA. It was hilarious and for what it's worth. Majin Buu as a saga and as a character ultimately sucked. TFS shouldn't have done the Majin Buu arc. That said the copyright claim nonsense and how you and Little Kuriboh capitulated to Toei animation is inexcusable. You guys singlehandedly revived DBZ and kept it going when Toei had no idea what to do with the show after it's run ended in the west. The fact that you didn't challenge these copyright claims when what you did was under fair use is still a weakness.

That said I will remain subscribed and I'm willing to see what you guys have up next. However, let this be a lesson. Never show weakness like this ever again.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm glad to see that you guys are getting a lot of support at the end of this tumultuous decision. snippet.textDisplay:
This may be a single person's opinion, but I will still provide it: thank you for everything you have given us. I'm not talking about dbza only either, Tfs gaming, ff7a, and many more. I love the creativity you guys bring to the table and it is my firm belief that, that same creativiti, should be nurtured and not stifled. If something is not fun, if something is not enjoyable to make, if it's forced then it needs to be stopped.
I honestly thank you, from the bottom of my heart, for dbza. It ignited the spark for dragon ball I completely forgot existed for years. But this not your end.
Because you loved it dbza became the masterpiece it is, só now show us what else you can do.
Im honesty looking forward to it.

snippet.textDisplay:
And now, the end is here
and so we face the final curtain.
My friends, they say it clear:
They state their case, of which they're certain.
It lived a life that's full,
It traveled each and every highway.
And more, much more than this
They did it their way.

Regrets, they've had a few,
but then again, too few to mention.
They did what they had to do
and saw it through without exemption.
They planned each charted course,
each careful step along the byway;
And more, much more than this
They did it their way.

Yes, there were times, they're sure we knew,
when they bit off more than they could chew.
But through it all, when there was doubt,

they ate it up and spit it out.
The record shows, they took the blows
And did it

their way!
